caption: Great food and excellent customer service !
The Wasabi and ranch wings were amazing! My daughter and I enjoyed the outside dinning which was amazing!  I would definitely return!
Hands down my favorite wings in the city! And the Fries are so clutch!

Stopped by here later in the night for a quick drink before they stop serving and I have no complaints the place seems awesome and definitely will be back earlier in the day to experience all it has to offer.

I went there last night to get some fried pickles and they literally were the best ever. I highly highly suggest eating here. Cool environment and great staff. Definitely a place I would come back too.

Do not order for catering!! I ordered 200 wings for the super bowl and missed kickoff because I waited 30 mins in the store to pick them up. It was obvious that they started my order when I got there even though I placed it 3 days in advance and called the morning of to confirm. I will not be returning to Tallboy.
Nice dive and great staff!

Absolutely loved this place- great snacks, great beer on draft and the service was 10/10! Great outdoor options for dining, we will be back!
Dope spot with GREAT DRINKS and GREAT WINGS!!!! The owner was super cool and nice!!! Safe place to get up with friends during this pandemic!  Will definitely be coming back!!

I didn't review this place when I got takeout from there over a year ago. So here it is.  This place is great.  I mean who doesn't like tallboys?  Who doesn't like grilled cheese?  No one I want to be friends with.  Also the staff is incredibly nice. So support these guys.

Love this place! It has a bit of a divey feel but with a good selection of tallboy beers and the food is grilled cheeses well done but not "fancy" and are reasonably priced. If your looking for a beer bar in the neighborhood this is your spot.
I love this place. 10/10
Great place delicious wings, I love Daryl and Ms Rain!

Awesome late night spot for late night team bonding and chatting with industry folk.

If you don't have Schlitz you don't have Gusto
They have really great happy hour. Love their grilled cheese, great selection of beers, quite affordable.
Been here once for happy hour. Had a grilled cheese. The food was great!

It’s tough to open up a “dive bar”. The best ones happen organically, so I was skeptical of a bar branding itself as a dive bar opening up in the Convention Center.  But it’s pretty good! $5 beers, happy hour deals, big TVs, and friendly bartender. Playlist features Little Brother and MF Doom which is alright with me.  I’d go back.

First time coming here early 2019, DIDNT think much of. In fact DIDNT even think would last.  Seemed small, too small, to last in current location. A quick walk north of the Marriott Marquis, Courtyard, and Rennaissance hotels - Convention Center - on 9th St NW.  Well guess what?  Still here, and STILL excellent.  Bar/ beer prices unmatched. $3 16oz Naragansetts for HH.  Great wings. And the best grilled cheese sandwiches around.  And opened till 2-3AM, including food until 1AM.  Nothing fancy.  Nothing special.  Just there, and fair- when and where nothing else is.  Highly recommended.  Take a look
Place is great
Katie is the BEST bartender. She took care of me and she provided EXCEPTIONAL service.
The place is cozy. Bartenders are friendly. Very good selection of beers. Happy hour is great.
One of the few literally no frills bars in DC. Super low key, cheap-ish happy hour, and amazing grilled cheese and wings.
Great place for a drink and a snack ate the grilled cheese too fast to get a pic

Chicken wings were amazing! Pretty small, but really friendly atmosphere. Highly recommend. . Ok, second day here and it is even better! Still great service supplied by Lorraine this time and the chicken wings are still amazing. This proves that they are consistently good. In addition, all of the other servers from the local bars come here when they close. It is the place to go!

I had an interesting grilled cheese  sandwich. It was vegetarian and included avocado, a black bean spread, onions, and of course lots of cheese. It was a tad bland for my tastes. The staff was very friendly!
No frills with a great vibe and service.
Very nice

Good cheap beer, chill atmosphere, cool bartenders, and eclectic and interesting TV options!

This is a great space from a great restaurant group in the city! The beer selection is excellently curated and the "fancy" grilled cheese is the perfect not-too-heavy bar food. The space looks bigger in person with a long bar and several hightop tables. When the sun goes down, the outside tables are very pleasant. And if you're not convinced yet, Daryl is one of the nicest bartenders I've ever met!
Daryl is the man
Chill spot to grab a tallboy and grilled cheese for the low - extra points for being open late
Fantastic experience.  A must try.
Great place to watch a game and have a couple beers. Seating is limited so be sure to plan ahead.

Such a great place to get some comfort food, watch a game OR play a board game. They have decent inexpensive beer, good wings and nice grilled cheese sandwiches!!! Great place to hang out with friends.
Really great bar.

Great new spot in Shaw for cheap eats and drinks! The tallboy beer offerings are great fun with a wide selection. We were promptly greeted by the staff and checked on periodically for beer emptiness needs. Bathrooms so clean (not like alot of places around). Grilled cheese was delicious and the old bay wings were likewise. They have card games and board games so it's a good date spot as well in a low key setting.
The Jameson is good here.
Nice chill, unpretentious bar in Shaw (which is rare). Inexpensive beers, solid wings, and cool bartenders. Good place to watch sports or hang out with friends.
Came here 3 times while on a business trip. Amazing grilled grilled cheese and beers.
